nexttext:
which is seen to be given by the frequency of the associated degenerate frequency with the leading correction
being second order in $s_\perp c / \omega^{(0)}$. 
As $\tau$ is increased beyond the threshold value 
for a particular location in wavevector space, the dominant change in the frequencies of the two bands is to acquire
imaginary components, with only minor shifts in the real components, which leaves the bands nearly flat after they merge.



















